## Why This Works — The Scheduler

```
JVM has a SCHEDULER (like a smart manager)

Ready Queue:  [VT-1] [VT-4] [VT-7] [VT-9] ...  ← waiting to run
Parked:       [VT-2] [VT-3] [VT-5] [VT-6] ...  ← blocked on I/O

Carrier Thread 1:
  1. Pick VT-1 from ready queue → mount → run
  2. VT-1 hits I/O → unmount → park VT-1
  3. Pick VT-4 from ready queue → mount → run
  4. VT-4 hits I/O → unmount → park VT-4
  5. I/O done for VT-1 → move VT-1 back to ready queue
  ...repeat forever
```

