## So Is It Async?

| | Async (CompletableFuture) | Virtual Threads |
|---|---|---|
| Code style | Callbacks / chains | Sequential / sync |
| Thread during block | Free (different thread) | Carrier free, VT parked |
| Concurrency | ✅ Yes | ✅ Yes |
| Readable code | ❌ Harder | ✅ Easier |
| True non-blocking | ✅ Yes | ❌ No (VT still waits) |

---

## Bottom Line

> Virtual threads achieve **concurrency without async code style.**
> One carrier thread can host **thousands to millions** of virtual threads dynamically.
> The number isn't fixed — it depends on **how often virtual threads block.**
> More blocking = more virtual threads a single carrier can juggle.
> They don't make code async — they make **blocking code scalable.**
